Fully qualified syntax does not seems to work for struct implementation:

```rust
pub trait VecContainer{
    type Item;
    fn get_mut(&mut self, index: usize) -> Option<&mut Self::Item>;
}

impl<T> VecContainer for Vec<T>{
    type Item = T;

    fn get_mut(&mut self, index: usize) -> Option<&mut T> {
        // !!! This actually calls VecContainer::get_mut()
        Vec::<T>::get_mut(self, index)
    }
}

fn test (vc: &mut impl VecContainer<Item = usize>){
    vc.get_mut(0);
}

fn main() {
    let mut v: Vec<usize> = vec![1,2,3];
    test(&mut v);
}
```

`Vec::<T>::get_mut(self, index)` actually calls `VecContainer::get_mut()` instead of Vec one's.

